            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>mayo</strong> with your <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> and <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) in a bowl</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (not a big garlic fan? Try using less!) with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>to the bowl and stir it all together – this is your<strong> spicy aioli</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1677698755825-x200.jpg",
