            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into rough, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped pepper</strong> and cook for 4-5 min, turning occasionally, until starting to char and soften – this is your <strong>charred pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
